WEBVTT

00:11.098 --> 00:13.187
Who else is on that
island? Victor?

00:13.317 --> 00:16.190
Nobody knows
where he is now.

00:16.320 --> 00:18.279
You're the best
and only shot to get

00:18.453 --> 00:20.977
their children
back from Padre.

00:21.151 --> 00:23.545
There are files that tell us
where you came from

00:23.719 --> 00:25.460
and who your parents are.

00:25.590 --> 00:27.723
[Glass shattering]

00:27.897 --> 00:30.421
We're going to find them,
and we're going to make Padre

00:30.552 --> 00:32.510
what it was meant to be
in the first place.

00:32.641 --> 00:35.557
<i>I repeat, my name</i>
<i>is Madison Clark.</i>

00:35.687 --> 00:38.255
<i>Come to</i>
<i>the following coordinates.</i>

00:38.429 --> 00:40.083
<i>Padre has fallen.</i>

00:40.127 --> 00:42.346
[Cheers and applause
in distance]

00:42.477 --> 00:46.176
♪♪

00:46.307 --> 00:48.309
[Cheering continues]

00:48.439 --> 00:53.836
♪♪

00:53.966 --> 00:57.100
[Spectators speaking German]

00:57.231 --> 00:58.971
[Speaking German]

00:59.102 --> 01:00.538
♪♪

01:00.669 --> 01:02.323
[Shouting in German]

01:02.453 --> 01:06.718
♪♪

01:06.849 --> 01:09.025
[Spectators cheering]

01:09.156 --> 01:11.288
[Speaking German]

01:11.419 --> 01:12.768
[Whistle blows]

01:12.898 --> 01:14.248
[Speaking German]

01:14.378 --> 01:16.163
[All cheering]

01:16.293 --> 01:22.995
♪♪

01:23.126 --> 01:29.872
♪♪

01:30.002 --> 01:36.879
♪♪

01:38.315 --> 01:40.100
[Speaking German]

02:03.340 --> 02:04.472
Aw!

02:06.169 --> 02:08.128
[Clicking tongue]

02:30.846 --> 02:32.500
[Knock on door]

02:36.330 --> 02:38.680
[Walkers growling in distance]

02:38.810 --> 02:46.296
♪♪

02:46.427 --> 02:53.912
♪♪

02:54.043 --> 02:56.176
[Growling continues]

02:59.744 --> 03:01.964
[Speaking German]

03:02.094 --> 03:04.053
I'm sorry?

03:06.490 --> 03:07.970
English, Klaus.

03:08.100 --> 03:11.278
What my son is trying to ask you
is if you needed help.

03:11.408 --> 03:13.105
I think it's infected,
but, um,

03:13.236 --> 03:15.369
I've been looking all over
for antibiotics, but...

03:15.499 --> 03:18.372
Well, you've come
to the right place.

03:19.677 --> 03:22.376
[Growling continues]

03:22.506 --> 03:24.073
Elderly Man:
What exactly is it?

03:24.204 --> 03:27.381
♪♪

03:27.511 --> 03:31.298
An oasis for the dispossessed,
the desperate, the weary.

03:33.082 --> 03:34.997
What exactly
does that mean?

03:35.127 --> 03:38.957
♪♪

03:39.088 --> 03:39.958
We help people.

03:40.089 --> 03:41.960
<i>Ah, guten tag.</i>

03:42.091 --> 03:46.051
[People conversing in German]

03:46.182 --> 03:48.358
Elderly Man: Why is everyone
speaking German?

03:48.489 --> 03:50.230
Frank:
We were tourists visiting this place

03:50.360 --> 03:51.927
when the world changed.

03:52.057 --> 03:53.755
The bus outside
was our tour bus.

03:53.885 --> 03:57.280
We never made it home,
so we decided to build one here.

03:57.411 --> 03:59.064
We got a second chance.

03:59.195 --> 04:03.982
This place is about making sure
other people get one, too.

04:04.113 --> 04:05.941
Everyone deserves
a second chance.

04:06.071 --> 04:14.210
♪♪

04:14.341 --> 04:16.256
[Indistinct shouting
in distance]

04:16.386 --> 04:24.873
♪♪

04:25.003 --> 04:26.962
Strand:
How you doing? You doing good?

04:27.092 --> 04:30.270
- Have you eaten?
- No, I haven't.

04:30.400 --> 04:31.532
Well, come on, then.

04:31.662 --> 04:33.969
[Growling]

04:34.099 --> 04:36.450
[Indistinct conversations]

04:36.580 --> 04:44.371
♪♪

04:44.501 --> 04:52.204
♪♪

04:52.335 --> 04:54.294
Strand:
There you go.

04:54.424 --> 04:55.686
How's the arm?

04:55.817 --> 04:57.122
The infection's
starting to clear.

04:57.253 --> 04:58.602
Oh, good.

04:58.733 --> 05:00.169
Eat up.

05:00.300 --> 05:02.998
The schnitzel will do wonders
for your strength.

05:03.128 --> 05:05.217
[Speaking German]

05:16.359 --> 05:18.709
Eat up.
It's homemade.

05:28.066 --> 05:30.547
[Wheezing, coughing]

05:32.854 --> 05:36.292
[Wheezing, gasping]

05:36.423 --> 05:37.902
Victor?

05:38.033 --> 05:40.165
♪♪

05:40.296 --> 05:42.254
No, it can't be...

05:43.430 --> 05:45.562
[Speaking German]

05:48.130 --> 05:49.479
H-His name is Anton.

05:49.610 --> 05:51.742
[Speaking German]

05:54.615 --> 05:55.659
Go.

05:55.790 --> 06:01.099
♪♪

06:01.230 --> 06:06.627
♪♪

06:06.757 --> 06:09.281
Say something, Victor.

06:09.412 --> 06:11.109
What are you doing here?

06:11.240 --> 06:13.764
♪♪

06:13.895 --> 06:16.854
And why was he
calling you Anton?

06:16.985 --> 06:19.204
And why are you
speaking German?

06:19.335 --> 06:21.381
Victor, answer me.

06:21.511 --> 06:28.997
♪♪

06:29.127 --> 06:36.657
♪♪

06:36.787 --> 06:38.441
[Madison sobs]

06:38.572 --> 06:40.356
I thought I lost you.

06:40.487 --> 06:46.928
♪♪

06:47.058 --> 06:53.543
♪♪

06:53.674 --> 06:55.284
What's going on, Victor?

06:55.415 --> 06:56.459
Frank: Anton?

06:56.590 --> 06:59.984
♪♪

07:00.115 --> 07:01.638
Anton?

07:01.769 --> 07:05.990
♪♪

07:06.121 --> 07:07.252
Is everything okay,
Anton?

07:07.383 --> 07:09.864
Madison:
His name's not Anton.

07:09.994 --> 07:11.735
It's Victor Strand.

07:11.866 --> 07:13.128
♪♪

07:13.258 --> 07:14.738
Tell them.

07:14.869 --> 07:17.088
♪♪

07:17.219 --> 07:18.481
My name is Anton.

07:18.612 --> 07:20.004
I've never heard
of Victor Strand.

07:20.135 --> 07:22.833
You must be mistaken.

07:22.964 --> 07:26.141
He's not telling the truth
about who he is.

07:26.271 --> 07:27.882
So you don't know
this woman?

07:28.012 --> 07:32.495
♪♪

07:32.626 --> 07:34.149
I've never seen her before
in my life.

07:34.279 --> 07:35.672
[Wheezing] What are you
talking about?

07:35.803 --> 07:37.065
You...
[Inhales sharply]

07:37.195 --> 07:38.370
[Thud]

07:38.501 --> 07:42.723
[Frank speaking German]

07:42.853 --> 07:44.507
Anton! Anton!

07:44.638 --> 07:51.819
♪♪

07:51.949 --> 07:59.261
♪♪

08:00.305 --> 08:03.657
♪♪

08:03.787 --> 08:06.181
[Speaking German]

08:23.981 --> 08:26.201
[Switch clicks, static]

08:26.331 --> 08:28.682
Daniel [over walkie]:
<i>Madison, are you there?</i>

08:28.812 --> 08:30.161
<i>Madison.</i>

08:30.292 --> 08:32.250
<i>Madison, do you copy?</i>

08:32.381 --> 08:35.819
<i>Who were those people...?</i>

08:35.950 --> 08:37.734
<i>I'm trying to track them down.</i>

08:37.865 --> 08:40.868
<i>Tell me where you are so I can</i>
<i>get to you before they do.</i>

08:40.998 --> 08:44.349
Is Madison blonde, about 5'6",
leather jacket?

08:44.480 --> 08:46.308
<i>And who am I talking to?</i>

08:46.438 --> 08:48.136
Someone who wants
to help her.

08:48.266 --> 08:51.356
<i>If you want to help me,</i>
<i>give me your location.</i>

08:51.487 --> 08:53.358
[Walkie beeps]
Anton.

08:53.489 --> 08:55.535
[Speaking German]

09:03.978 --> 09:08.722
♪♪

09:08.852 --> 09:15.163
♪♪

09:20.516 --> 09:27.479
♪♪

09:27.610 --> 09:29.046
Klaus.

09:30.874 --> 09:34.486
♪♪

09:48.196 --> 09:53.897
♪♪

09:54.028 --> 09:59.816
♪♪

09:59.947 --> 10:01.426
[Moans lightly]

10:01.557 --> 10:03.733
[Dove cooing]

10:11.654 --> 10:12.655
Hey.

10:14.048 --> 10:16.050
Ah.
You're awake.

10:16.180 --> 10:17.791
Yeah.

10:17.921 --> 10:19.923
You mind cutting me loose?

10:22.360 --> 10:24.711
My dad said
it's not safe.

10:24.841 --> 10:26.147
Oh.

10:26.277 --> 10:28.192
What do <i>you</i>think?

10:36.505 --> 10:40.204
So, uh, why do you think
my dad's this Victor Strand guy?

10:42.685 --> 10:44.426
Because he is.

10:44.556 --> 10:47.124
I know my dad.
He wouldn't lie.

10:47.255 --> 10:49.910
You don't know Victor.

10:50.040 --> 10:52.521
Why would he pretend
to be somebody he's not?

10:52.652 --> 10:54.479
[Sighs]

10:54.610 --> 10:56.220
Actually,
I don't know.

10:56.351 --> 10:58.483
But it's really
pissing me off.

11:08.406 --> 11:10.670
Who's Nick and Alicia?

11:11.888 --> 11:13.760
They were my kids.

11:13.890 --> 11:15.979
Mm. Were?

11:20.549 --> 11:22.159
I'm sorry.

11:25.119 --> 11:27.295
They rescued a bird once too
when they were about your age,

11:27.425 --> 11:29.079
maybe a little younger.

11:31.734 --> 11:33.475
They, uh, get confused

11:33.605 --> 11:36.739
and fly into the hotel windows
sometimes.

11:36.870 --> 11:38.741
And you always help them?

11:38.872 --> 11:41.048
Everyone deserves
a second chance.

11:43.137 --> 11:45.095
Who taught you that?

11:45.226 --> 11:46.749
My dad.

11:46.880 --> 11:48.577
Anton.

11:54.452 --> 11:57.325
Where's your mother?

11:57.455 --> 11:59.719
Uh...

11:59.849 --> 12:03.070
She and Papa split up
when I was little.

12:03.200 --> 12:04.811
He, uh, he brought me here
on a holiday

12:04.941 --> 12:07.683
just before
the world changed.

12:07.814 --> 12:09.685
But...

12:09.816 --> 12:13.210
those are as close as I got
to seeing beyond this hotel.

12:13.341 --> 12:15.996
We, uh,
we got stuck here.

12:16.126 --> 12:19.782
And we've been here
ever since.

12:19.913 --> 12:21.697
I never saw Mama again.

12:25.222 --> 12:27.007
I'm sure she'd be
so proud of you.

12:30.184 --> 12:32.882
You seem cool too.

12:33.013 --> 12:35.624
I don't think everyone agrees
with you.

12:35.755 --> 12:37.844
The people
who attacked you?

12:37.974 --> 12:39.715
We listened
to your walkie.

12:39.846 --> 12:42.457
Is that
why you came here?

12:42.587 --> 12:43.632
Yeah.
Why are they after you?

12:43.763 --> 12:45.416
Honestly,
I'm not sure.

12:45.547 --> 12:47.592
They hit us out of nowhere,
stole our boats.

12:47.723 --> 12:49.377
You must've done
<i>something</i>to them.

12:49.507 --> 12:50.639
Strand:
Klaus.

12:50.770 --> 12:53.207
♪♪

12:53.337 --> 12:54.469
[Speaking German]

12:54.599 --> 12:56.558
I have to hand it to you,
Victor.

12:56.688 --> 12:58.299
Anton.

12:58.429 --> 13:00.127
Really made something here,
you know,

13:00.257 --> 13:02.129
even if it is
all a lie.

13:02.259 --> 13:04.435
He's not lying.

13:04.566 --> 13:06.829
Here's the thing
I don't get.

13:06.960 --> 13:08.700
Why like this?

13:08.831 --> 13:10.180
Why are you hiding?

13:10.311 --> 13:12.313
[Frank speaking German
over walkie]

13:15.620 --> 13:18.145
[Frank speaking]

13:18.275 --> 13:19.320
What's going on?

13:19.450 --> 13:21.975
♪♪

13:22.105 --> 13:23.846
How can we be
of service?

13:23.977 --> 13:25.369
We're looking
for a woman.

13:25.500 --> 13:27.502
We heard she's hiding out
in the area.

13:27.632 --> 13:30.984
Well, that doesn't
narrow it down.

13:31.114 --> 13:32.681
Her name's Madison.

13:32.812 --> 13:34.770
♪♪

13:34.901 --> 13:36.816
What do you want
with her?

13:36.946 --> 13:38.426
That's our business.

13:38.556 --> 13:41.168
♪♪

13:41.298 --> 13:43.648
I'm afraid
we can't help.

13:43.779 --> 13:45.520
You have children
in there?

13:48.915 --> 13:50.090
Some.

13:50.220 --> 13:51.961
Well, this woman,

13:52.092 --> 13:54.529
she used to be
one of PADRE's top collectors.

13:54.659 --> 13:57.358
She's been broadcasting
how she's trying to rebuild it.

13:57.488 --> 13:58.750
That seems
like a good thing.

13:58.881 --> 14:02.102
[Chuckles]
<i>Seems</i>ain't is.

14:02.232 --> 14:05.018
This particular leopard
don't change her spots.

14:05.148 --> 14:06.758
How would you know?

14:06.889 --> 14:10.414
The people I'm with,
the head of this little outfit?

14:10.545 --> 14:13.809
He knows her
for who she really is.

14:13.940 --> 14:16.029
Daniel [over walkie]:
<i>Whoever you are,</i> <i>I know you're listening.</i>

14:16.159 --> 14:17.595
<i>I know this is the channel</i>
<i>you were moni--</i>

14:17.726 --> 14:19.075
[Walkie beeps]

14:21.512 --> 14:24.689
I'm sorry, but like I told you
before, she isn't here.

14:24.820 --> 14:26.822
♪♪

14:26.953 --> 14:28.737
I think she is.

14:28.868 --> 14:31.087
Which means there are two ways
this can go.

14:31.218 --> 14:32.610
And what are those?

14:32.741 --> 14:34.874
♪♪

14:35.004 --> 14:39.704
One, you let us in,
hand her over, we walk away.

14:39.835 --> 14:41.402
And the other?

14:41.532 --> 14:44.535
The voice you heard
on the radio, he's not alone.

14:44.666 --> 14:46.146
And from our limited dealings
with him,

14:46.276 --> 14:48.496
he seemed
pretty determined.

14:48.626 --> 14:50.977
We'll fight him if we have to
to get to her.

14:51.107 --> 14:53.805
♪♪

14:53.936 --> 14:56.199
Now, if that's a fight
you want on your doorstep...

14:56.330 --> 15:02.466
♪♪

15:02.597 --> 15:08.777
♪♪

15:08.908 --> 15:10.735
She's here.

15:10.866 --> 15:13.738
Anton, what the hell?

15:13.869 --> 15:15.175
Anton. Anton.

15:15.305 --> 15:16.654
♪♪

15:19.614 --> 15:21.659
♪♪

15:21.790 --> 15:23.618
Klaus!

15:25.141 --> 15:26.490
Klaus!

15:26.621 --> 15:32.844
♪♪

15:32.975 --> 15:34.498
Where the hell is she?
Frank: She's gone.

15:34.629 --> 15:36.631
They both are.

15:36.761 --> 15:38.589
She took him.

15:38.720 --> 15:40.591
I told you
she seemed dangerous.

15:40.722 --> 15:44.421
We need to move.
If she gets him back to PADRE...

15:44.552 --> 15:46.249
you'll never see
your son again.

15:46.380 --> 15:49.818
♪♪

15:49.949 --> 15:51.907
That's not
where they're going.

15:52.038 --> 15:53.387
This is.

15:53.517 --> 15:55.041
She tore the map off
before she left.

15:55.171 --> 15:56.564
Frank: Why would she
take him there?

15:56.694 --> 15:58.522
Only one way
to find out.

15:58.653 --> 16:08.402
♪♪

16:08.532 --> 16:10.012
We came in
on two of these.

16:10.143 --> 16:11.753
She must've taken
the other one.

16:11.883 --> 16:13.363
They can't be
that far ahead of us.

16:13.494 --> 16:15.670
Let's move.

16:15.800 --> 16:17.367
Your weapons.

16:17.498 --> 16:18.673
Just to be safe.

16:18.803 --> 16:20.457
Safe for who?

16:20.588 --> 16:22.677
We'll give them back to you once
we get to where we're going.

16:22.807 --> 16:27.856
♪♪

16:27.987 --> 16:29.292
Daniel [over walkie]:
<i>Hello, Madison.</i>

16:29.423 --> 16:31.294
<i>Madison, are you there?</i>

16:31.425 --> 16:33.818
Listen, old man,
that place you've got?

16:33.949 --> 16:35.995
You're gonna be
better off without her.

16:36.125 --> 16:39.346
<i>Hurting her would be</i>
<i>a grave mistake.</i>

16:39.476 --> 16:41.739
What happens to her
ain't up to me.

16:41.870 --> 16:44.177
Things will go a lot better
for her and for you if you back off.

16:44.307 --> 16:46.135
<i>It's too late for that.</i>

16:46.266 --> 16:54.056
♪♪

16:54.187 --> 16:56.928
Shit, he found us.

16:57.059 --> 16:58.365
Get in the boat.

16:58.495 --> 17:00.584
♪♪

17:00.715 --> 17:03.065
Let's go. We leave now,
we can still lose him!

17:03.196 --> 17:07.548
♪♪

17:07.678 --> 17:08.940
Ugh!

17:09.071 --> 17:11.030
♪♪

17:11.160 --> 17:12.074
[Frank speaking German]

17:12.205 --> 17:14.163
Anton!

17:14.294 --> 17:16.296
♪♪

17:16.426 --> 17:18.167
Screw this.

17:18.298 --> 17:28.134
♪♪

17:28.264 --> 17:29.961
[Speaking German]

17:42.409 --> 17:44.367
[Walkers growling]

17:44.498 --> 17:47.805
♪♪

17:47.936 --> 17:49.459
[Knife stabs]

17:49.590 --> 17:51.505
[Body thuds]

17:56.553 --> 17:59.730
So, are you going to say it
or are you going to make me ask?

17:59.861 --> 18:02.298
Why English?
I want to hear it as you think it.

18:02.429 --> 18:05.606
That woman, why does
she have you so upset?

18:05.736 --> 18:07.347
She has our son, Frank.

18:07.477 --> 18:09.044
I mean before that.

18:09.175 --> 18:10.959
She got under your skin
from the minute she showed up.

18:11.090 --> 18:12.178
She called me
someone else.

18:12.308 --> 18:14.310
Well? Are you?

18:14.441 --> 18:15.920
How could you
ask me that?

18:16.051 --> 18:18.619
I know you haven't been
fully honest with me.

18:18.749 --> 18:20.273
I've always known.

18:20.403 --> 18:22.449
You think I don't know
what it is to live a lie?

18:22.579 --> 18:24.451
All the years I spent
living with Mia,

18:24.581 --> 18:27.323
hiding from her who I was,
from Klaus.

18:29.195 --> 18:31.545
Whatever's going on,
you can tell me.

18:31.675 --> 18:38.073
♪♪

18:38.204 --> 18:39.466
There it is.

18:39.596 --> 18:45.776
♪♪

18:45.907 --> 18:47.430
How did you know
that was here?

18:47.561 --> 18:50.999
I used it years ago,
before we found each other.

18:51.130 --> 18:52.653
The years haven't been
kind to it.

18:52.783 --> 18:54.524
We're going to have to walk
the rest of the way.

18:54.655 --> 18:56.265
Come.

18:56.396 --> 18:58.659
I need you to go back
to the hotel.

18:58.789 --> 19:00.356
He's our son.
I'm coming with you.

19:00.487 --> 19:02.880
Please.
Let me do this alone.

19:03.011 --> 19:04.926
[Walker growling]

19:05.056 --> 19:09.060
♪♪

19:09.191 --> 19:11.193
[Knife stabs]

19:11.324 --> 19:12.716
[Body thuds]

19:12.847 --> 19:14.718
Hey!
What are you doing?

19:14.849 --> 19:17.591
[Walkers growling]
Strand: Frank!

19:17.721 --> 19:19.114
[Body thuds]

19:22.030 --> 19:23.727
Frank:
You're hiding something.

19:23.858 --> 19:26.165
♪♪

19:26.295 --> 19:28.123
Are you that man
she talked about?

19:28.254 --> 19:30.169
Are you Victor Strand?

19:31.213 --> 19:32.345
Answer me!

19:32.475 --> 19:33.650
Frank!

19:33.781 --> 19:35.652
[Walker growling]

19:35.783 --> 19:37.654
♪♪

19:37.785 --> 19:39.961
[Frank grunts]

19:40.091 --> 19:41.180
[Blade stabs]

19:41.310 --> 19:44.531
♪♪

19:44.661 --> 19:47.229
Where the hell did
that come from?

19:47.360 --> 19:49.275
It's what
I was looking for.

19:49.405 --> 19:52.974
[Growling]

19:53.104 --> 19:55.498
We should move. Now.

19:58.893 --> 20:02.201
[Walker growling]

20:02.331 --> 20:04.507
Anton.
[Blade stabs]

20:04.638 --> 20:07.336
[Body thuds]

20:07.467 --> 20:09.686
[Sighs] There was nothing
we could've said

20:09.817 --> 20:12.776
that would've
made him stay.

20:12.907 --> 20:14.952
Why?

20:15.083 --> 20:17.216
She reminds him
of his mother.

20:18.565 --> 20:20.175
How?

20:20.306 --> 20:23.309
Klaus wasn't there for her
when the world changed.

20:23.439 --> 20:25.398
He was here.

20:25.528 --> 20:27.269
Maybe Madison made him feel
like he had

20:27.400 --> 20:29.315
a second chance
at helping her.

20:29.445 --> 20:31.534
[Insects chirping]

20:39.107 --> 20:42.110
You never told me
what happened

20:42.241 --> 20:44.286
after you told her
your truth.

20:48.551 --> 20:51.380
She was angry.

20:51.511 --> 20:53.077
And confused.

20:53.208 --> 20:55.297
♪♪

20:55.428 --> 20:57.560
In the end,
the truth set us free.

20:57.691 --> 21:02.043
♪♪

21:02.173 --> 21:04.567
I should've
come clean sooner.

21:04.698 --> 21:08.789
♪♪

21:08.919 --> 21:11.357
She forgave you?

21:11.487 --> 21:13.010
Of course.

21:13.141 --> 21:15.143
♪♪

21:15.274 --> 21:17.188
Just as I would you.

21:17.319 --> 21:21.367
♪♪

21:21.497 --> 21:23.586
What are you
talking about?

21:23.717 --> 21:26.241
♪♪

21:26.372 --> 21:27.938
If you are
Victor Strand.

21:28.069 --> 21:29.418
I'm not.
But...

21:29.549 --> 21:31.028
if you are.

21:31.159 --> 21:33.727
♪♪

21:33.857 --> 21:38.122
Whatever you did,
I'm sure it's forgivable.

21:38.253 --> 21:44.172
♪♪

21:44.303 --> 21:46.000
I'm not that man.

21:46.130 --> 21:52.833
♪♪

21:54.313 --> 21:55.879
[Walkers growling in distance]

21:56.010 --> 21:57.925
There it is.

21:58.055 --> 22:00.144
The library
from the tour map.

22:01.711 --> 22:03.800
[Growling continues]

22:03.931 --> 22:05.585
They're here.

22:10.894 --> 22:12.592
They're just like the raft
in the woods.

22:12.722 --> 22:13.723
[Blade scrapes]

22:13.854 --> 22:14.855
Come on.

22:19.033 --> 22:21.122
Klaus: Wake up.

22:21.252 --> 22:23.951
Wake up, wake up.

22:24.081 --> 22:26.432
It's gonna be okay.
Just stay with me.

22:26.562 --> 22:27.694
[Door opens]

22:27.824 --> 22:28.956
Frank: Klaus?

22:29.086 --> 22:30.349
Dad! Papa!

22:34.962 --> 22:36.442
[Door closes]

22:40.228 --> 22:43.971
[Speaking German]

22:56.984 --> 22:58.725
Frank: Klaus.

22:58.855 --> 23:01.380
[Speaking German]

23:08.517 --> 23:09.910
Strand: Ah!

23:39.287 --> 23:41.594
[Engine whirring in distance]

23:50.820 --> 23:51.865
Okay.

23:52.822 --> 23:53.954
Klaus.

24:17.194 --> 24:18.500
Anton.

24:25.507 --> 24:26.682
Klaus.

24:27.770 --> 24:33.515
♪♪

24:38.520 --> 24:47.747
♪♪

24:47.877 --> 24:57.234
♪♪

25:17.907 --> 25:23.826
♪♪

25:23.957 --> 25:30.093
♪♪

25:32.313 --> 25:41.757
♪♪

25:44.499 --> 25:51.593
[Oxygen hissing]

25:51.724 --> 25:53.769
Strand: [Whispering]
We need to go.

25:56.990 --> 25:59.558
What are you doing here?
Where's Klaus?

25:59.688 --> 26:01.908
I sent Klaus away
with Frank.

26:02.038 --> 26:04.693
So you can throw me
to the wolves again?

26:04.824 --> 26:07.566
The wolves are circling.
I came here to help you.

26:08.567 --> 26:09.655
Since when?

26:09.785 --> 26:11.918
Since I promised my son
I would.

26:14.747 --> 26:17.314
You can either come with me
and live...

26:18.881 --> 26:20.491
...or stay here and die.

26:25.279 --> 26:27.368
Strand:
We need to get to the dock. We can take their Zodiac.

26:27.498 --> 26:30.153
Then what?
We can talk about that once we clear this place.

26:30.284 --> 26:32.416
You wouldn't even protect me
at your own settlement, Victor.

26:32.547 --> 26:33.853
My name is Anton.

26:33.983 --> 26:35.332
You scared shitless
your little family

26:35.463 --> 26:37.291
is gonna find out
who you really were?

26:37.421 --> 26:38.684
They know who I am.

26:38.814 --> 26:40.773
So much so that you were ready
to let me die

26:40.903 --> 26:43.645
just to protect
your secret.

26:43.776 --> 26:45.647
I'm here, aren't I?

26:45.778 --> 26:47.475
You gonna cut my throat
with that sword?

26:47.606 --> 26:48.824
No.

26:48.955 --> 26:51.392
Go back, tell your kid
those people did it?

26:51.522 --> 26:52.698
[Wheezes]

26:52.828 --> 26:54.177
I'm not who you think.

26:54.308 --> 26:55.831
I don't even know who the hell
you are anymore.

26:55.962 --> 26:57.877
[Gun cocks]

26:59.922 --> 27:02.055
Found you.

27:02.185 --> 27:03.883
And you.

27:05.319 --> 27:06.668
Don't do this.

27:06.799 --> 27:09.279
Whatever she did,
we can work it out.

27:09.410 --> 27:11.804
Whatever she did?
Yeah.

27:11.934 --> 27:15.024
You have no idea how far back
this goes, do you?

27:15.155 --> 27:18.245
Why are you doing this?
I don't even know who you are.

27:18.375 --> 27:20.421
But we know you,
Madison.

27:20.551 --> 27:23.729
Whoever you think she is,
that's not her anymore.

27:23.859 --> 27:25.644
Believe me, I know.

27:25.774 --> 27:28.821
Believe you?
After what you pulled on us?

27:28.951 --> 27:30.866
You two are the same.

27:30.997 --> 27:33.303
Both pretending to be
something you're not.

27:33.434 --> 27:34.957
I'm not fooled
by either one of you.

27:35.088 --> 27:37.046
Come on, let's go.
For what?

27:37.177 --> 27:38.613
What do you want?

27:38.744 --> 27:40.484
PADRE.

27:40.615 --> 27:44.358
We've been looking for a place
like it for a long time.

27:44.488 --> 27:46.186
You're gonna show us
where it is.

27:46.316 --> 27:49.580
[Walkers growling]

27:49.711 --> 27:51.539
[Gunshots, blade clattering]

27:51.670 --> 27:52.932
Strand: Let's go!

27:54.716 --> 27:57.197
Russell:
They're getting away!

27:57.327 --> 27:59.068
Come on.

27:59.199 --> 28:00.722
Over there!

28:00.853 --> 28:02.811
[Gunshots]

28:02.942 --> 28:07.163
♪♪

28:07.294 --> 28:09.905
The boat.

28:10.036 --> 28:11.254
We're not gonna make it.

28:11.385 --> 28:13.213
♪♪

28:13.343 --> 28:14.954
Down there!
[Gunshot]

28:15.084 --> 28:16.695
We have to go back.

28:16.825 --> 28:18.740
[Walkers growling]

28:18.871 --> 28:27.009
♪♪

28:27.140 --> 28:28.968
[Blade stabs]

28:29.098 --> 28:31.274
The path, go, go, go!

28:31.405 --> 28:33.407
[Growling continues]

28:33.537 --> 28:36.889
♪♪

28:37.019 --> 28:38.238
Aah!

28:38.368 --> 28:39.674
It's not gonna hold!

28:39.805 --> 28:41.371
Is there
a back way out? No.

28:41.502 --> 28:43.025
Madison,
the bookshelf!

28:43.156 --> 28:46.899
♪♪

28:47.029 --> 28:48.291
Now!

28:48.422 --> 28:50.467
♪♪

28:50.598 --> 28:52.121
[Both grunting, panting]

28:52.252 --> 28:53.862
Now![Grunts]

28:53.993 --> 28:58.084
♪♪

28:58.214 --> 29:00.173
[Growling]

29:00.303 --> 29:04.351
♪♪

29:04.481 --> 29:06.048
[Blade stabs]

29:06.179 --> 29:09.269
♪♪

29:09.399 --> 29:12.446
[Grunting]

29:12.576 --> 29:14.709
[Gunshots]

29:17.059 --> 29:18.147
I'm out.

29:18.278 --> 29:21.324
Frank, Klaus,
we need your help!

29:21.455 --> 29:23.500
Oh, shit. Oh.

29:23.674 --> 29:25.720
[Growling]

29:27.940 --> 29:29.376
I'm so sorry.

29:29.506 --> 29:31.160
Is that you talking
or Anton?

29:31.291 --> 29:33.641
It's me, Madison.

29:33.772 --> 29:35.556
Whatever I call myself.

29:35.686 --> 29:37.471
Why are you pretending
to be someone else?

29:37.601 --> 29:39.299
Because I had to.

29:39.429 --> 29:42.563
Because I had to leave
that person behind.

29:42.693 --> 29:44.304
What did you do,
Victor?

29:44.434 --> 29:47.655
I did what I had to do to build
a thriving tower,

29:47.786 --> 29:49.875
a place
people could be safe.

29:50.789 --> 29:52.791
[Wood creaking]

29:54.880 --> 29:57.317
I was ruthless.
Even to Alicia.

29:57.447 --> 29:58.753
I betrayed her, Madison.

29:58.884 --> 30:00.581
And when the tower fell,
we all washed up

30:00.711 --> 30:02.061
on these shores,
and we got separated.

30:02.191 --> 30:03.714
Some were taken
to PADRE.

30:03.845 --> 30:06.805
Others were -- were struggling
to survive out here.

30:06.935 --> 30:09.895
I tried to help them,
but they wouldn't let me.

30:10.025 --> 30:12.549
They couldn't forgive me.

30:12.680 --> 30:15.770
I tried to help them find food.
To make amends.

30:15.901 --> 30:18.947
When I came back...

30:19.078 --> 30:22.908
they were dead,
just like them.

30:23.038 --> 30:26.215
I hated being
Victor Strand.

30:26.346 --> 30:27.651
So I killed him.

30:27.782 --> 30:29.044
As far as
I was concerned,

30:29.175 --> 30:31.568
he died with everyone else
that day.

30:31.699 --> 30:33.919
What did you become?

30:34.049 --> 30:35.616
Who are you?

30:35.746 --> 30:38.140
♪♪

30:38.271 --> 30:41.927
The last time
I saw Alicia...

30:42.057 --> 30:45.017
she told me
that she loved me.

30:45.147 --> 30:48.759
I didn't think
anyone could.

30:48.890 --> 30:52.285
I met Frank and Klaus,
and they changed everything.

30:52.415 --> 30:55.549
I could be the person
that Alicia thought I could be.

30:55.679 --> 30:57.638
[Wood creaking]

30:57.768 --> 31:00.380
But I could only do it
as someone else.

31:00.510 --> 31:02.643
As Anton.

31:02.773 --> 31:05.385
I understand.

31:05.515 --> 31:07.039
Klaus is a good kid.

31:07.169 --> 31:08.997
♪♪

31:09.128 --> 31:11.043
I'd say you did alright.

31:11.173 --> 31:15.743
♪♪

31:15.874 --> 31:16.962
Thank you.

31:17.092 --> 31:20.269
[Growling]

31:20.400 --> 31:23.664
Alicia had the chance
to let me die.

31:23.794 --> 31:26.580
And after everything I did,
I deserved it.

31:26.710 --> 31:29.496
But she didn't.

31:29.626 --> 31:31.715
Why didn't she?

31:33.674 --> 31:35.197
Because her mother
taught her

31:35.328 --> 31:37.199
that no one is gone
until they're gone.

31:37.330 --> 31:39.506
♪♪

31:39.636 --> 31:43.031
That everyone deserves
a second chance.

31:43.162 --> 31:44.685
No matter what.

31:44.815 --> 31:47.688
♪♪

31:47.818 --> 31:50.343
We're not so different,
Victor.

31:50.473 --> 31:53.694
PADRE, the people
that were running it,

31:53.824 --> 31:55.304
we got rid of them.

31:55.435 --> 31:56.958
I promised those kids.

31:57.089 --> 31:59.743
♪♪

31:59.874 --> 32:02.181
Kids that I took there
when I was a Collector,

32:02.311 --> 32:05.749
I promised them I'd help them
find their parents.

32:05.880 --> 32:08.448
I started sending out messages
on long range,

32:08.578 --> 32:10.798
from the repeater station,
just...

32:10.929 --> 32:12.495
just trying to get them
as far as I could,

32:12.626 --> 32:16.369
just hoping that
some parents would hear me.

32:16.499 --> 32:18.849
Did they?
Some.

32:18.980 --> 32:22.114
Some, but they weren't
the only ones listening.

32:22.244 --> 32:24.203
♪♪

32:24.333 --> 32:30.296
Those people heard my broadcast,
drew them right to me.

32:30.426 --> 32:33.168
And now I've put everyone else
in danger because of it.

32:33.299 --> 32:35.866
[Growling intensifies]

32:35.997 --> 32:39.087
You were just
trying to help.

32:39.218 --> 32:43.831
That place, what I promised
those kids...

32:43.962 --> 32:45.659
that's all I have left,
Victor.

32:45.789 --> 32:48.357
♪♪

32:48.488 --> 32:50.838
[Klaus speaking German
over walkie]

32:52.622 --> 32:53.667
Klaus.

32:57.149 --> 32:59.934
♪♪

33:00.065 --> 33:02.241
[Growling]

33:02.371 --> 33:03.982
[Gunfire]

33:04.112 --> 33:04.983
Down!

33:05.113 --> 33:09.509
[Gunfire continues]

33:09.639 --> 33:15.428
♪♪

33:15.558 --> 33:21.390
♪♪

33:21.521 --> 33:23.044
Klaus [over walkie]:
<i>Dad? Hurry.</i>

33:23.175 --> 33:25.090
<i>You need</i>
<i>to get back here.</i>

33:25.220 --> 33:27.353
Don't worry.
We'll take you to them.

33:30.660 --> 33:32.314
[Sounds distorting]

33:32.445 --> 33:34.316
[Breath echoing]

33:34.447 --> 33:37.754
♪♪

33:37.885 --> 33:40.496
Russell: [Distantly]
Welcome back.

33:40.627 --> 33:42.194
What is this?

33:42.324 --> 33:44.805
[Breathing heavily]

33:44.935 --> 33:46.676
Klaus, Frank.

33:46.807 --> 33:47.808
Dad!
What?

33:47.938 --> 33:49.114
What?

33:49.244 --> 33:50.506
[Grunts]

33:52.552 --> 33:54.728
I told you
to hand her over.

33:54.858 --> 33:57.296
This could all
have been avoided.

33:57.426 --> 33:58.993
If you hurt them...

33:59.124 --> 34:01.691
It's like I said before.
It's not up to me.

34:01.822 --> 34:04.085
Then who's it up to?

34:04.216 --> 34:05.565
I'll let him tell you.

34:05.695 --> 34:08.481
[Door opens, closes]

34:08.611 --> 34:12.615
♪♪

34:12.746 --> 34:13.834
Man:
Hey there, Madison.

34:13.964 --> 34:15.879
[Breathing heavily]

34:16.010 --> 34:19.666
♪♪

34:19.796 --> 34:21.537
Been a while.

34:21.668 --> 34:23.191
[Dramatic music plays]

34:23.322 --> 34:24.584
Troy.

34:24.714 --> 34:27.500
Yeah, see, I'm as surprised
as you are.

34:27.630 --> 34:29.241
I mean,
I knew I'd find you

34:29.371 --> 34:33.027
when I heard your radio
broadcast, but, uh...

34:33.158 --> 34:35.160
I didn't think
you'd still be keeping

34:35.290 --> 34:39.120
the same company
from Mexico.

34:39.251 --> 34:40.991
Frank:
You're making a mistake.

34:41.122 --> 34:42.819
He's not who you think.

34:42.950 --> 34:44.778
♪♪

34:44.908 --> 34:47.694
That's not
Victor Strand?

34:47.824 --> 34:50.175
His name is Anton.

34:50.305 --> 34:52.481
You're confused.

34:52.612 --> 34:54.135
My eyesight's not
what it once was,

34:54.266 --> 34:57.921
I'll give you that, my friend,
but, uh...

34:58.052 --> 34:59.923
I think you're the one
that's confused.

35:00.054 --> 35:02.143
♪♪

35:02.274 --> 35:03.971
About him...

35:04.102 --> 35:06.104
and certainly
about her.

35:06.234 --> 35:10.804
♪♪

35:10.934 --> 35:13.111
These are the people
that took her in, right?

35:13.241 --> 35:15.200
♪♪

35:15.330 --> 35:18.377
Good.
You know what?

35:18.507 --> 35:20.727
I'm gonna tell you the truth
about who she is.

35:20.857 --> 35:22.337
In fact, you know what?

35:22.468 --> 35:24.600
Even better.

35:24.731 --> 35:27.125
Let me, uh...
Let me show you.

35:27.255 --> 35:30.084
♪♪

35:30.215 --> 35:32.042
See that?

35:32.173 --> 35:35.263
I know it's not very pretty
to look at.

35:35.394 --> 35:37.178
Can happen, though.

35:37.309 --> 35:42.705
Take a bad hit to the head
from, say, uh, a hammer.

35:42.836 --> 35:51.453
♪♪

35:51.584 --> 36:00.070
♪♪

36:00.201 --> 36:02.160
Which is what
she did to me...

36:02.290 --> 36:06.686
♪♪

36:06.816 --> 36:10.255
...before she just left me
for dead in Mexico.

36:10.385 --> 36:13.606
And that's after she destroyed
my family's ranch.

36:13.736 --> 36:15.477
Can you believe that?

36:15.608 --> 36:17.784
♪♪

36:17.914 --> 36:20.656
My brother...
My father...

36:20.787 --> 36:23.398
♪♪

36:23.529 --> 36:25.705
I lost them all
because of her.

36:25.835 --> 36:27.576
♪♪

36:27.707 --> 36:29.230
And he helped.

36:29.361 --> 36:34.670
♪♪

36:34.801 --> 36:36.368
What do you want, Troy?

36:36.498 --> 36:37.978
[Chuckles lightly]
Oh...

36:38.108 --> 36:39.327
Oh, same thing
I've wanted

36:39.458 --> 36:42.765
since you took it
from me, Madison.

36:42.896 --> 36:46.465
Same thing I've been helping
all these good people find

36:46.595 --> 36:49.816
since I pulled myself
out of the rubble in Mexico.

36:49.946 --> 36:52.906
I'm just looking for a home,
Madison.

36:53.036 --> 36:54.690
You see,
you took mine from me,

36:54.821 --> 36:57.258
so I'm gonna
take yours from you.

36:57.389 --> 36:59.739
You're never gonna
find it.

36:59.869 --> 37:01.088
Yeah, I will.

37:01.219 --> 37:03.133
Oh, yeah?
How?

37:03.264 --> 37:05.005
'Cause you're gonna
tell me.

37:05.135 --> 37:07.703
♪♪

37:07.834 --> 37:12.099
Or I'm gonna do to him
what you did to me.

37:12.230 --> 37:13.535
Aah!

37:13.666 --> 37:15.233
Please, please, please.

37:15.363 --> 37:16.321
Don't do it, Madison.

37:16.451 --> 37:18.061
Victor, Victor!
No, no, no!

37:18.192 --> 37:20.107
Don't tell them.
Hold onto that place.

37:20.238 --> 37:22.588
It's what Alicia
would've wanted.

37:22.718 --> 37:25.243
Please! Let him go.
Don't hurt him.

37:25.373 --> 37:26.983
Tell him
what he wants to know.

37:27.114 --> 37:29.072
I would listen to him, Madison,
because if you don't,

37:29.203 --> 37:31.249
I'm not gonna stop
with him, am I?

37:31.379 --> 37:34.948
So, how many more people
are you prepared to hurt?

37:35.078 --> 37:37.124
Anton, look at me.

37:37.255 --> 37:45.611
♪♪

37:45.741 --> 37:49.484
My name is Victor Strand.

37:49.615 --> 37:56.143
♪♪

37:56.274 --> 37:59.451
I lied to you
about so much.

37:59.581 --> 38:01.714
But what I felt for you
was real.

38:01.844 --> 38:06.632
♪♪

38:06.762 --> 38:09.025
[Speaking German]

38:09.156 --> 38:13.639
♪♪

38:13.769 --> 38:15.728
- No.
- Alright.

38:15.858 --> 38:17.077
Time's up, Madison.

38:17.207 --> 38:19.166
- No.
- Aah!

38:19.297 --> 38:21.821
Drop the hammer!

38:21.951 --> 38:25.477
Now!

38:25.607 --> 38:26.739
Drop it.

38:26.869 --> 38:28.001
Do it!

38:28.131 --> 38:30.003
♪♪

38:30.133 --> 38:31.657
Strand:
June...Sherry...

38:31.787 --> 38:35.965
♪♪

38:36.096 --> 38:37.750
Drop your weapon.

38:37.880 --> 38:40.883
I suggest you follow
your own advice, old timer.

38:41.014 --> 38:42.842
[Hammer clatters]

38:42.972 --> 38:44.670
[Body thuds]

38:44.800 --> 38:50.980
♪♪

38:51.111 --> 38:52.199
Thank you,
old friend.

38:52.330 --> 38:53.679
We're not friends.

38:53.809 --> 38:55.898
Hate to do to you
what I did to your daughter.

38:56.029 --> 38:59.641
♪♪

38:59.772 --> 39:00.860
Troy Otto.

39:00.990 --> 39:03.993
♪♪

39:04.124 --> 39:05.560
Hm.

39:05.691 --> 39:08.258
Next time, I'm gonna make sure
you really die.

39:08.389 --> 39:09.869
You really think what you're
doing right now

39:09.999 --> 39:11.610
is gonna stop us?

39:11.740 --> 39:17.006
♪♪

39:17.137 --> 39:18.878
We know where
this place is now.

39:19.008 --> 39:21.315
We're just gonna keep
coming back.

39:21.446 --> 39:22.708
Yeah, you do that, Troy,

39:22.838 --> 39:24.884
and there won't be anyone here
for you to hurt.

39:25.014 --> 39:26.973
The place you want,
the place I'm building,

39:27.103 --> 39:29.889
it's about to expand.

39:30.019 --> 39:31.891
You all took me in
when I needed help.

39:32.021 --> 39:33.719
Now I'm doing
the same for you.

39:33.849 --> 39:35.895
♪♪

39:36.025 --> 39:38.811
I just told you
what she did to me.

39:38.941 --> 39:41.466
What makes you think she's not
gonna do the same to you?

39:43.076 --> 39:45.600
I won't pretend I haven't done
things I regret.

39:45.731 --> 39:48.821
But the place I'm building,
it's not about me.

39:48.951 --> 39:52.041
It's about keeping
something bigger alive.

39:52.172 --> 39:53.782
And what's that?

39:53.913 --> 39:55.915
Daniel: Madison, we don't know
how many people he has.

39:56.045 --> 39:57.873
We have to get out.
My kids.

39:58.004 --> 40:00.572
I'm gonna build that place into
what it should've always been,

40:00.702 --> 40:03.183
for them, for Alicia.

40:03.313 --> 40:06.186
Well, you can do that.
You're making a mistake.

40:06.316 --> 40:08.144
Let's move on!

40:08.275 --> 40:09.798
Why is that?

40:09.929 --> 40:15.238
♪♪

40:15.369 --> 40:17.545
'Cause that's the same thinking
that got her killed

40:17.676 --> 40:20.200
in the first place.

40:20.330 --> 40:22.550
How the hell would you know?

40:22.681 --> 40:24.726
'Cause I'm the one
that killed her.

40:24.857 --> 40:26.989
You're a liar!

40:27.120 --> 40:28.687
Don't believe me?

40:28.817 --> 40:33.735
♪♪

40:33.866 --> 40:35.171
Open it.

40:35.302 --> 40:38.436
♪♪

40:38.566 --> 40:41.177
Don't listen to him.
Let's get outta here.

40:41.308 --> 40:48.620
♪♪

40:48.750 --> 40:56.062
♪♪

40:56.192 --> 40:57.933
What is this?

40:58.064 --> 41:02.634
♪♪

41:02.764 --> 41:04.244
Troy:
You don't recognize it?

41:04.374 --> 41:06.202
♪♪

41:06.333 --> 41:07.552
It belonged to Alicia.

41:07.682 --> 41:11.077
♪♪

41:11.207 --> 41:13.558
I took it off her corpse
after I killed her.

41:13.688 --> 41:22.958
♪♪

41:23.089 --> 41:32.446
♪♪

41:32.577 --> 41:34.100
Aaah!
No, Madison!

41:34.230 --> 41:37.277
Madison!
You! Aah!

41:37.407 --> 41:39.192
Don't!

41:39.322 --> 41:41.586
Don't let him
get in your head.

41:41.716 --> 41:44.632
See, I would've
put her down, Madison.

41:44.763 --> 41:46.765
After all the wandering around
I did in Mexico,

41:46.895 --> 41:50.159
I thought it was only right
that Alicia should do the same.

41:50.290 --> 41:52.901
You know, maybe one day
you'll find her.

41:53.032 --> 41:55.077
Or maybe she'll find you,
or maybe not,

41:55.208 --> 41:58.298
and finish the job.

41:58.428 --> 42:00.735
You want a fight, Madison?
We'll give you that.

42:00.866 --> 42:02.432
We'll give you a fight.

42:02.563 --> 42:04.739
♪♪

42:04.870 --> 42:07.829
My question for you is...

42:07.960 --> 42:10.310
what are you even
fighting for?

42:10.440 --> 42:16.838
♪♪

42:20.712 --> 42:21.930
Madison, wait.
Someone has got to stop him.

42:22.104 --> 42:22.888
Let me come with you.

42:23.062 --> 42:24.759
What's going on?
I got it.

42:24.890 --> 42:27.762
Doesn't look like it.

42:27.893 --> 42:29.111
Alicia was in the herd.

42:29.285 --> 42:31.418
Madison: I need to
put her to rest.

42:31.592 --> 42:34.073
Then you can build PADRE
into what Alicia wanted.

42:34.203 --> 42:35.553
Strand:
Where are you going?

42:35.683 --> 42:37.903
To kill Troy.

42:38.077 --> 42:39.121
Troy: <i>Victor?</i>

42:39.252 --> 42:41.080
Troy. We need
a place to live.

42:41.254 --> 42:43.125
Help me find PADRE.

42:43.299 --> 42:44.779
Strand: He's going to hit us
with everything he's got.

42:44.997 --> 42:47.086
♪♪

42:47.260 --> 42:49.915
I'm gonna strangle him
with my bare hands!

42:50.045 --> 42:52.265
Why do you care
so much about PADRE?

42:52.395 --> 42:53.875
Because you took everything
from me.

42:54.049 --> 43:01.274
♪♪♪

43:06.627 --> 43:11.893
♪♪

43:12.024 --> 43:15.505
[Speaking German]

43:15.636 --> 43:18.204
[Speaking German]

43:18.334 --> 43:20.946
What we see in the beginning
of this episode

43:21.076 --> 43:24.602
is that Victor Strand has
completely reinvented himself.

43:24.732 --> 43:26.255
You've come
to the right place.

43:26.386 --> 43:29.258
There is no trace
of the old Strand whatsoever.

43:29.389 --> 43:32.000
He's going by a new name.
His name is Anton.

43:32.131 --> 43:33.959
He's speaking German.

43:34.089 --> 43:36.918
He has a new husband.
He has a son.

43:37.049 --> 43:39.704
He has this whole community
that he's built.

43:39.834 --> 43:45.013
And Madison coming into that
story is an earthquake for him.

43:45.144 --> 43:47.276
Victor?

43:47.407 --> 43:51.193
It's a major threat
not only to his livelihood,

43:51.324 --> 43:53.369
but truly the life
that he's set up for himself

43:53.500 --> 43:55.458
and his future.

43:55.589 --> 43:59.462
♪♪

43:59.593 --> 44:02.030
It's taking him deeply back
into his past.

44:02.161 --> 44:03.858
Madison:
What are you doing here?

44:03.989 --> 44:06.513
Dickens: It's almost like
her world starts to spin.

44:06.644 --> 44:08.428
And why was he
calling you Anton?

44:08.558 --> 44:11.736
When she sees this man
that is Victor Strand,

44:11.866 --> 44:14.608
he looks different,
he's got different clothes on,

44:14.739 --> 44:18.481
but Madison is like,
"That's Victor Strand."

44:18.612 --> 44:19.831
And she lets him have it.

44:19.961 --> 44:22.181
His name's not Anton.

44:22.311 --> 44:24.400
It's Victor Strand.

44:24.531 --> 44:27.621
There is a shift
in this episode for Madison

44:27.752 --> 44:30.580
to move towards
trusting Victor again.

44:30.711 --> 44:32.495
It's not gonna hold!

44:32.626 --> 44:35.324
And I think forgiveness
comes because Madison does --

44:35.455 --> 44:37.283
seeing their similarities.

44:37.413 --> 44:41.026
They both feel that,
through each other,

44:41.156 --> 44:42.592
they can honor Alicia.

44:42.723 --> 44:45.204
And, of course,
the moment they do that,

44:45.334 --> 44:47.293
they realize that's gonna be
even harder than they thought

44:47.423 --> 44:49.295
when Troy Otto resurfaces.

44:49.425 --> 44:50.992
See that?

44:51.123 --> 44:52.864
Dickens:
It was an incredible character.

44:52.994 --> 44:56.084
And I always loved the dance
that Madison and Troy did,

44:56.215 --> 44:57.825
and I look forward
to more of that.

44:57.956 --> 44:59.392
Which is what
she did to me...

44:59.522 --> 45:04.397
♪♪

45:04.527 --> 45:06.616
- Roll two cameras!
- Rolling!

45:06.747 --> 45:09.924
♪♪

45:10.055 --> 45:12.710
Being a director means you have
to wear so many different hats.

45:12.840 --> 45:15.495
You have to have your eye
on so many different things,

45:15.625 --> 45:18.063
so many more
than you do as an actor.

45:18.193 --> 45:21.806
And Danay just came in
and attacked it with grace,

45:21.936 --> 45:24.939
and she was able to deliver
a fantastic episode.

45:25.070 --> 45:28.334
You have to direct
an entire world.

45:28.464 --> 45:32.512
You get to see it from all kinds
of dimensions, and I loved that.

45:32.642 --> 45:33.948
That was, for me, the challenge.

45:34.079 --> 45:35.820
Man: Roll! Steady!
Rolling!

45:35.950 --> 45:37.647
It was a beautiful experience.

45:37.778 --> 45:40.912
I'm just looking for a home,
Madison.

45:41.042 --> 45:42.652
You see,
you took mine from me,

45:42.783 --> 45:45.220
so I'm gonna
take yours from you.

45:45.351 --> 45:46.918
Aah!

45:47.048 --> 45:48.876
Please, please, please.
Don't do it, Madison.

45:49.007 --> 45:51.096
They crack Strand open
in that scene,

45:51.226 --> 45:53.402
and Strand confesses his lies.

45:53.533 --> 45:55.361
♪♪

45:55.491 --> 45:58.494
My name is Victor Strand.

45:58.625 --> 46:01.628
♪♪

46:01.759 --> 46:03.456
He's just laid bare.

46:03.586 --> 46:06.154
I lied to you
about so much.

46:06.285 --> 46:09.157
But what I felt for you
was real.

46:09.288 --> 46:12.291
He has true love with Frank.

46:12.421 --> 46:14.510
That is what I believe
that they have.

46:14.641 --> 46:17.905
♪♪

46:18.036 --> 46:19.559
And in one scene he says,

46:19.689 --> 46:22.214
"If you are Victor Strand,
I'll forgive you."

46:22.344 --> 46:24.216
I do think that that's
one of the greatest

46:24.346 --> 46:26.522
expressions of love and of grace

46:26.653 --> 46:28.698
and belief in your fellow man --

46:28.829 --> 46:30.831
that everyone can be redeemed.

46:30.962 --> 46:35.880
♪♪

46:36.837 --> 46:41.799
♪♪

46:43.322 --> 46:52.984
♪♪

46:53.114 --> 47:02.907
♪♪

47:03.037 --> 47:12.873
♪♪
